				charm of the scene. The dominant hues of yellows and blues create a
				sense of inviting warmth, while the contrasting shadows add depth and
				dimension to the composition.
			</p>
			<p>
				The composition of "Cafe Terrace" is carefully balanced, with the
				central focus on the café itself. Van Gogh skillfully leads the viewer's
				gaze towards the brightly lit terrace, drawing attention to the patrons
				seated at the tables. The curving lines of the cobblestone street and
				the awning above the café create a sense of movement and guide the eye
				through the painting. The overall effect is an immersive experience that
				invites the viewer to imagine themselves in the vibrant ambiance of the
				café.
			</p>
